1
00:00:02,868 --> 00:00:06,868
The person next to us, 
they have their karmic circumstance,

2
00:00:07,068 --> 00:00:09,248
their sojourn
in the material world

3
00:00:09,248 --> 00:00:11,592
that’s brought them
to this particular point

4
00:00:11,592 --> 00:00:13,402
and time, place,
and circumstance.

5
00:00:13,602 --> 00:00:18,362
[How to Find Inner Peace]

6
00:00:18,636 --> 00:00:23,746
We have to accept that
for the most part.

7
00:00:23,797 --> 00:00:28,018
And if the Paramātmā
is non‒interfering,

8
00:00:28,018 --> 00:00:29,628
the Paramātmā,

9
00:00:29,628 --> 00:00:34,768
the Super-soul, 
the Over-soul,

10
00:00:34,768 --> 00:00:37,018
is not meddling
in the situation,

11
00:00:37,018 --> 00:00:44,088
because that would be 
to interfere with the jīva‒soul’s

12
00:00:44,088 --> 00:00:47,418
minute independence.

13
00:00:47,708 --> 00:00:50,932
There can be suggestion, 
but not interference.

14
00:00:50,932 --> 00:00:54,542
What does 
the Upaniṣads say?

15
00:00:56,690 --> 00:00:59,310
dvā suparṇā sayujā sakhāyā
[Upaniṣads: 4.6]

16
00:00:59,310 --> 00:01:01,190
in one place.

17
00:01:01,198 --> 00:01:06,338
Like two birds on a tree. 
The tree is karmic activity.

18
00:01:06,338 --> 00:01:08,588
One bird is 
the individual soul,

19
00:01:08,588 --> 00:01:12,498
the other bird is 
the Super-soul, Paramātmā,

20
00:01:12,498 --> 00:01:16,688
overseer, observer,
who is observing jīva

21
00:01:16,688 --> 00:01:23,968
as she tastes the fruits 
of karmic activity.

22
00:01:23,968 --> 00:01:30,688
So, sometimes
Śrīla Guru Mahārāj would say ...

23
00:01:30,688 --> 00:01:35,838
If you can embrace 
this concept.

24
00:01:35,838 --> 00:01:41,288
And it’s thematically resurfaces 
at different times in Bhagavad-gītā:

25
00:01:41,288 --> 00:01:46,296
bhoktāraṁ yajña-tapasāṁ 
sarva-loka-maheśvaram
 

26
00:01:46,296 --> 00:01:51,326
suhṛdaṁ sarva-bhūtānāṁ 
jñātvā māṁ śāntim ṛcchati
[Bg: 5.29]

27
00:01:51,326 --> 00:01:56,841
It says, “jñātvā māṁ—knowing this, 
what's just been described—if you know this,

28
00:01:56,841 --> 00:02:03,091
then śānti;
Om śānti, śānti, śānti ...

29
00:02:03,091 --> 00:02:05,251
You can get a little bit 
of peacefulness in the world,

30
00:02:05,251 --> 00:02:09,241
if you understand 
that in the background

31
00:02:09,241 --> 00:02:14,274
that person for whom we say,
as, again, the aphorism says,

32
00:02:14,274 --> 00:02:20,664
“Not a blade of grass moves
without the will of God.”

33
00:02:20,664 --> 00:02:23,698
It obviously moves 
without our consent.

